Crackers

Preheat oven to 400F.

- 1 cup all-purpose flour
- 1/2 tsp salt
- 2 Tbsp butter
Place flour, salt and butter into food processor with bread blade. Pulse until combined.

- About 1/4 cup water
Add 1/4 cup water and pulse to blend.
Continue adding water if necessary, a little bit at a time, just until mixture holds together but is not sticky.

Roll out onto wax paper until 1/4 inch thick or less. Add small amounts of flour if necessary.

- Sea salt
Place into lightly floured baking sheet, and score with a sharp knife.  Sprinkle with salt to taste.

Bake until lightly browned, about 10 minutes. Serve hot.


